# Customer profile — Threadlight onboarding intake

> **Move 1 of `threadlight-customize`.** Copy this file to
> `docs/threadlight-customize/customer-profile.md` and fill it in **with** the
> customer's cloud/platform owner. This is the single source of truth every
> later move reads. **Every unfilled field is a blocker, not a TODO** — a blank
> "private DNS zones" line will stop the deploy in Move 3.
>
> Fill-in markers are written as `_<…>_`. Replace them. Use `n/a` explicitly
> when a field genuinely does not apply (so a blank always means "not yet
> answered").

- **Customer / engagement:** _<name or anonymized code, e.g. "telco-emea-01">_
- **Date / SE:** _<date>_ / _<se alias>_
- **Operator path:** _<SE-led | customer-self-serve>_
- **Target go-live posture:** _<pilot-to-prod | net-new prod | parallel run>_

---

## Block A — Customer documents (collect, then link)

Link each document into the engagement repo (or note where it lives). Do not
paraphrase from memory — get the artifact.

- [ ] **Cloud architecture / reference architecture** — _<link or "received">_
- [ ] **Security & governance policy** (Azure Policy set, allowed SKUs/regions,
      tagging standard) — _<link>_
- [ ] **Network topology** (hub/spoke, VNets, subnets, firewall/egress, private
      DNS) — _<link>_
- [ ] **Naming & tagging standard** — _<link>_
- [ ] **Identity model** (Entra tenant, PIM, managed-identity policy, who can
      grant RBAC) — _<link>_
- [ ] **Compliance / data residency** (in-scope regulations, data classes,
      allowed geographies) — _<link>_
- [ ] **Change-management / approval process** (who signs off a prod deploy,
      gates, freeze windows) — _<link>_

> If a document does not exist, write that explicitly — its absence is itself a
> finding for the architecture review.

## Block B — Environment setup (drives every override)

This block and Block D drive Move 2. Do not start Move 2 until this is complete.

- **Subscription(s) / management group:** _<sub id(s), MG path>_
- **Landing zone type:** _<CAF platform LZ | application LZ | standalone sub | other>_
- **Target resource group(s):** _<rg name(s) or "to be created by platform team">_
- **Allowed regions:** _<region allow-list>_
- **Network exposure:** _<public | private-endpoints | fully-private VNet, no egress>_
- **VNet / subnet for the workload:** _<vnet/subnet ids or "to be provisioned">_
- **Private DNS zones in use:** _<list, e.g. privatelink.openai.azure.com,
  privatelink.blob.core.windows.net, privatelink.documents.azure.com,
  privatelink.vaultcore.azure.net>_
- **Egress / firewall posture:** _<NSG/Azure Firewall/UDR notes; allowed FQDNs>_
- **Deploy identity model:** _<UAMI + OIDC/WIF | SP | PIM-elevated human; who owns it>_
- **Who can assign RBAC (and at what scope):** _<role/owner>_
- **Central platform dependency:** _<none | consume existing Citadel hub |
  hub-deploy-then-spoke>_  → if not "none", this is a `threadlight-cicd` +
  `citadel-spoke-onboarding` concern, not this skill's.
- **Foundry / AOAI account:** _<existing account + region, or to be created>_
- **Container registry (ACR):** _<existing or to be created; private?>_
- **State / data stores in scope:** _<Cosmos, Storage, AI Search, Key Vault — ids/regions>_

## Block C — Requirements

- **Primary process / use-case:** _<one paragraph>_
- **Functional requirements:** _<list or link to SPEC>_
- **Non-functional requirements:** _<latency, availability, throughput, RTO/RPO>_
- **Compliance gates that block go-live:** _<list>_
- **HITL / approval requirements:** _<SPEC § 8 actions needing human gates>_
- **Observability / SRE expectations:** _<who operates it, what they need>_
- **Success criteria for "onboarded":** _<measurable definition of done>_

## Block D — Mandated template / starter code (build ON this, not around it)

Customers frequently require you to build on **their** IaC and pipeline
templates, not greenfield. Capture what you must reuse; these become overlay
inputs in Move 2.

- **Mandated IaC modules / golden modules:** _<repo/registry + which modules>_
- **Required pipeline templates** (GitHub Actions / Azure DevOps shared
  templates): _<repo + template paths>_
- **Required base images / build standards:** _<registry, base image policy>_
- **Required repo/branch/PR policy:** _<protected branches, required reviewers>_
- **Bring-your-own constraints** (anything that overrides a Threadlight
  default): _<list>_

